column5: I talk to my girl friends about that stuff all the time.
Good points, thank you.
Yeah it's just frustrating.. I didn't want to be friends, but she got mad, and now we are friends but it seems like we still aren't friends because she can't even talk about her boyfriend or dating.

So many options, how do I choose? :) None of them are great.

I guess it's just a black box that I'll never know the contents of because I can't really ask.

Appreciate the insight.
Yeah, it's just weird. I have female friends and we always discuss their relationships/boyfriends and relationship dynamics in general just because it is an interesting subject.
She actually does have a boyfriend, yeah could just be the latter, but it is weird she won't even talk about dating dynamics in general.

> but it seems in your case you won't be able to move on.

Yeah, I thought I would. At first I tried to cut off contact which failed because she got mad, now I am in close contact and it is just as bad, and quarantine is not helping either.

> you're a person and you deserve someone who cares about you.

I agree, I really don't know why I am hung up on this girl, but I can't really control it.
Probably. I don't know, you tell me? :)

> that you're still into her and haven't let go of how you feel. Asking someone out one time does not mean you're perp

I agree for the most part, but what do you suggest I do? I still have to her almost everyday. I tried cutting off contact with her but she got pissed at me.

Hah, good points.

We are just friends, but only because she won't go out with me - does that make you happy? :)

But what am I supposed to do? I tried not to be friends with her. I didn't want to be friends with her, but she pushed for it. I see her all the time. Now here I am.
It's not negative context at all.
We are just friends. She wanted to be friends initially, not me. Is it a dick move just to talk to a girl with a boyfriend?

She knows that I am into her, I asked her out.

> Find a new person who is into you too and wants to spend time on you.

It is good advice, thank you.
I thought about that too, but it seems like if you are traveling to a park just to meet someone when you could just walk where you live then I'm not sure it is essential anymore?
"if you have to ask" ðŸ˜‚

Not really supposed to be going to meet up with other people you are not sheltering-in-place with, and even if you did you would need to stay 6 feet apart. I think it would be considered non-essential travel, so probably very much discouraged.
What do you do on your video dates?
What do you do on your video dates?
What is the alternative then, just wait till the lockdown is over and keep the text conversation going till then?

I feel for you - sending hugs your way <3

It's crazy for me to think that you could be obsessed with such a thing, but that makes me realize that must be how people must feel about my obsession.

Makes me feel better and hopeful, hope that perspective helps you as well - thanks for sharing. :)
Really good idea for storing the box folded underneath my bed - thanks!
Still have a long road ahead of me, but it's nice to have hope and start to get a semblance of it back
Was the extra cost significant?
Thanks, didn't realize it was such a hassle with moving companies. Probably will end up keeping the box.

It can be so, so convincing and I still struggle to separate the two.

I feel for you man - I also have already had a heart ultrasound, EKG, 24 hour heart rate monitor, etc.

The obsession changes all the time which I am only realizing now.. it used to be dry eyes, leg edema, blurry night vision, dark circles, extreme tiredness, arm sweating, etc. all which have ebbed and flowed/resolved on their own and never actually represented disease.

I'm just tired of trying to "solve" my health problems at this point I am trying to just go with the doctors and let things balance out over time, trying to ignore what I "perceive" as health problems along the way if my doctor says there is nothing to worry about.

> ving companies have boxes and padding specifically designed to transport TVs. You should ask your moving company how they handle TVs.

That's the problem, I don't know which moving company I will go with.

I agree, it doesn't seem the box was meant for re-use, but at least the styrofoam even without the box seems like it would be really useful for just surrounding the Tv. Doesn't seem like the box itself is of much use at all.

That is actually very comforting, and so true. It is an obsession thing, and if it wasn't heart disease for me it would be something else. The content of the obsession isn't really relevant. It just whatever our brain decides to "stick" onto.

Thanks for sharing your story - it is comforting to know there are other people going through similar issues. :)

> Needless to say, not sure if you find this yourself, but my brain is so â€œpowerfulâ€ that it manifests symptoms and pain, further exacerbating the obsession. Now, I say powerful because that actually is what has helped me prep for not just labor, but also has helped me frame this disorder in a way that brings me peace. If my brain can be so powerful as to manifest pain/symptoms, then it can do the opposite, right? That has been a huge step in the right direction for my recovery.

That's an excellent way of putting it. I actually have a very similar issue.. been having really bad heart pounding/palpitations/chest tightness which my doctor thinks is due to stress/anxiety and I obsess over it because of my obsession with heart disease, and like you said it just makes everything worse and it is a vicious cycle.

This is great, thank you so much. I definitely haven't taken that route yet.

I am starting to realize that stating there is nothing to worry about is also a compulsion. Better to accept the uncertainty and accept I've done everything I rationally can and move on from the thought.

Very easy to miss that as a compulsion.

Oh damn, that is crazy. I didn't have any detectable abnormalities. It is just perceived for me.. so I don't think ablation is an option. Glad you got it figured out.. insane to have that many detectable palpitations!
True, good point - thanks.
I don't think I can contribute more to Roth IRA just because I contributed to Roth 401k?
It reduces the amount I can contribute to my traditional 401k.
It's Roth 401k, not Roth IRA, that is the problem.
That's what I figured - would be a nightmare for my employer to figure out. Thanks.
Yes.

Yeah, unfortunately mine has been going on well before this, but it sure hasn't helped. Keeping myself busy is a big help.

Unfortunately, I live alone. At least we have other on the internet which I am thankful for. 

Hope your palpitations improve soon. ðŸ»

AFAIK it will just decrease what I can contribute to my traditional since the max contribution for all 401k combined (traditional + roth) is the same as for each individual account if you had not made any contributions to the other one.

Yes - please share! ðŸ™‚

I agree it is very challenging to separate heart palpitations from disease but the reality is there isn't much of a link as far as I understand if there are not other symptoms present - for example I do tons of high intensity exercise with no chest pain, etc.

> you are not alone

Thanks for your kind words - sending much love. â¤ï¸

Sending love your way man - treat yourself well in these tough times.

One thing that really has been helping me in a pinch is diaphragmatic breathing maybe it can help you out too if you aren't already using it.
YES! And it means I can never relax. I have forgotten how to do so.
You got it! Thanks.
Would that be recommended even for a C9 owner?
Your legs are 6ft long? How tall are you, 12ft? :)
Good call out, slanted might be an option but the sound would be going slightly outwards - probably not a huge deal though..

>  as you. 65â€ vizio, elac debut 2 b5.2â€™s, and 71â€ stand. My speakers each hang off the tv stand about 3/4â€ but theyâ€™re not going anywhere. The wife hated the idea of speaker stands so this was 

Nice! Exact same situation! Did you consider putting them slightly behind the TV and slanting them outwards a bit?
Yikes, I just ordered the TV stand it isn't even here yet.. I thought I was going to go for 55 inch TV so it is my fault but I'm hoping it doesn't come to that.

> But let me tell you what the future holds. Things will be less expensive with more features.

LOL good point.
Right, but there are lots of bikes that are both? Like the Juiced Scrambler has a throttle but throttle only can only go 20mph, and also has PAS with max 28mph. That is where I am confused.

Agreed, though it seems like it should be able to be both. If it meets both definitions and as long as you stick to Class 3 and above friendly roads I don't see the issue, even if the law was to get very pedantic about it.
Yeah this is exactly what I am trying to protect against, thank you for the reminder.
I'm always confused by Class 3 vs. Class 2, are they mutually exclusive or can you have both in the same bike?

Very interesting, thanks for the extra information.

I wonder if I would be able to get the bottom of the range with zero pedaling?

Ah, I see!

Yeah I don't intend on using it as an actual bike.. I'd prefer not to pedal at all as I get enough exercise elsewhere in my life. Also the terrain is just mainly roads and sidewalks for me.
